# Common Patterns

## Repository pattern

Encapsulate data access behind a consistent interface so business logic doesn’t depend on storage details. This improves testability and enables swapping implementations (DB, API, file, cache).

## API response envelope (when applicable)

Use a consistent response shape across endpoints. Typical elements:

- **status/success** indicator
- **data** payload (nullable on error)
- **error** message/code (nullable on success)
- **metadata** for pagination (cursor/page/limit/total), when listing resources

